---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 6 — "backoff + jitter" (Level 10).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component because inline SVG
 * with kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Retries with exponential backoff and jitter: synchronized retries collide; jitter smears them into smooth load"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="140"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">NO JITTER — herd retries collide</text
            >
            <line x1="20" y1="110" x2="260" y2="110" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <g stroke="#9a2417" stroke-width="2.5">
                <line x1="70" y1="110" x2="70" y2="48"></line><line x1="73" y1="110" x2="73" y2="48"
                ></line><line x1="76" y1="110" x2="76" y2="48"></line>
                <line x1="150" y1="110" x2="150" y2="60"></line><line
                    x1="153"
                    y1="110"
                    x2="153"
                    y2="60"></line><line x1="156" y1="110" x2="156" y2="60"></line>
                <line x1="220" y1="110" x2="220" y2="72"></line><line
                    x1="223"
                    y1="110"
                    x2="223"
                    y2="72"></line>
            </g>
            <text x="140" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >spikes at 1s, 2s, 4s</text
            >
            <line x1="288" y1="10" x2="288" y2="140" stroke="#d8d4c8" stroke-dasharray="4 4"></line>
            <text
                x="430"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">FULL JITTER — smooth load</text
            >
            <line x1="312" y1="110" x2="552" y2="110" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <g stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="2.5">
                <line x1="330" y1="110" x2="330" y2="88"></line><line
                    x1="352"
                    y1="110"
                    x2="352"
                    y2="82"></line><line x1="378" y1="110" x2="378" y2="90"></line>
                <line x1="404" y1="110" x2="404" y2="84"></line><line
                    x1="432"
                    y1="110"
                    x2="432"
                    y2="92"></line><line x1="460" y1="110" x2="460" y2="86"></line>
                <line x1="492" y1="110" x2="492" y2="90"></line><line
                    x1="524"
                    y1="110"
                    x2="524"
                    y2="88"></line>
            </g>
            <text x="432" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >random delay in [0, cap]</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Retries: only retry <em>idempotent</em> ops · back off exponentially · add <b>jitter</b> to break
        lockstep · circuit-break sustained failures. Full jitter both minimises competing calls and finishes
        fastest. (Brooker, AWS Builders' Library.)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
